This paper focuses on self-organization in the Internet of Things (IoT), which is a subfield of computer networking (cs.NI). The proposed framework is based on Network Formation Game, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the emergence of realistic topologies and stable multi-hop network structures, which are topics related to complex systems and self-organization (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis and design of mechanisms, which is a subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT).
